RStudio Debugging Webinar

The R language has a collection of packages, functions, and tools that can be used to help identify and diagnose errors in R code. The RStudio IDE provides easy access to many these tools to make the process of debugging easier for the R developer. This webinar highlights best practices for debugging R code in RStudio.

The data used in this webinar comes from opendata.utah.gov and contains hospital ratings data for hospitals in Utah.
